    <h2 id="shape-based">Shape-Based Measure Words: The Logic Behind the System</h2>
    <p>Chinese measure words are not random — many follow a shape-based logic that makes them predictable once you understand the pattern:</p>

    <div style="max-width:500px;margin:2rem auto;font-family:sans-serif">
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:12px;justify-content:center">
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:140px;background:#eff6ff;border:2px solid #3b82f6;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;text-align:center">
          <div style="font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:bold;color:#2563eb">条 tiáo</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#666;margin-top:4px">Long &amp; thin</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.9rem;margin-top:8px">fish · road · river · pants · snake · noodles</div>
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:140px;background:#f5f3ff;border:2px solid #7c3aed;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;text-align:center">
          <div style="font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:bold;color:#7c3aed">张 zhāng</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#666;margin-top:4px">Flat surface</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.9rem;margin-top:8px">paper · table · bed · photo · map · ticket</div>
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:140px;background:#ecfdf5;border:2px solid #059669;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;text-align:center">
          <div style="font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:bold;color:#059669">块 kuài</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#666;margin-top:4px">Chunk / piece</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.9rem;margin-top:8px">cake · bread · stone · soap · land · money</div>
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:140px;background:#fef2f2;border:2px solid #dc2626;border-radius:8px;padding:14px;text-align:center">
          <div style="font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:bold;color:#dc2626">粒 lì</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:#666;margin-top:4px">Tiny &amp; round</div>
          <div style="font-size:0.9rem;margin-top:8px">rice · pill · seed · pearl · sand · bullet</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>This shape-based logic means that even if you encounter a new noun, you can often make an educated guess about its measure word based on its physical shape. A long, thin object? Probably 条. A flat object? Probably 张. A small round thing? Probably 粒 or 颗.</p>

